race.comment: DECORUM (5) has two wins and a close second to Group 1 winner Attica in three starts. Resumed last time with a comprehensive victory over 1400m at this track, overcoming difficulties along the way. Should relish getting to the mile and makes plenty of appeal again. TAZIMA (1) got warm when the race was all over when resuming last time out over 1400m at Caulfield. Not a noted first-up performer to put the effort in context. Will take a lot from that outing and the extra furlong is a tick. LANCELOT DU LAC (2) is still in his first prep and the form is holding up. Chased home Unleeshing over the Randwick mile most recently. Hyeronimus has won two from two on the colt and he is back aboard. Big threat back in midweek company. AURA (11) won well over this distance at Goulburn last start. Significant step up in grade today but on the limit cannot be ruled out entirely. SIRIUS LEGEND (6) was plain here first-up. Fitter and far better placed out to the mile.
